      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Feeling invisible and replaceable is a gut-punch, especially when you used to shoulder most of the caregiving load. Remember, their stress isn't about resenting you, it's about juggling their own responsibilities. You haven't outlived your purpose, you've simply shifted roles, and it's time to accept that role might not be as central to their lives anymore. Try not to compare your importance to yours before – your kids care about you, even if they can't care for everything you need.",
      "source": "target",
